    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.3421/41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-23T13:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 23, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 24, 3.59 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. Department’s June 24, 2 p.m. Forwarded today in pouch number 20 by
                    cruiser <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi> text of Vickers Armstrong proposition,
                    which would close the open door, covering 55-year monopoly of construction steel
                    plant, shipyards, et cetera, with important ramifications. Itabira not
                    controlling factor in awarding contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
